{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make hair colour a protected characteristic to prevent discrimination",
        "additional_details": "Some people see bullying red-haired people is acceptable, but this is prejudice against people for a trait they were born with.\r\n \r\nWhilst some people might see it as a laugh to belittle, demean and abuse children for being red haired or their phenotypical characteristic, it can be very harmful stripping these children of their positive self-identity and confidence and worse it can lead to school refusal, health problems, and even self-injurious behaviour.\r\n",
        "background": "Extend discrimination protection in the Equality Act to hair colour, to try and help prevent discrimination and bullying of people for their hair colour.",
